theorem dense_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A ‚Üí Topology.P3 A := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hx
  have hClosure : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa using hDense.closure_eq
  have : x ‚àà (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    trivial
  simpa [hClosure, interior_univ] using this

theorem closure_interior_union_subset_union_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ‚à™ B)) ‚äÜ
      closure (interior A) ‚à™ closure (interior B) := by
  intro x hx
  -- Rewrite the interior of the union as a union of interiors.
  have hInt : interior (A ‚à™ B) = interior A ‚à™ interior B := by
    simpa using interior_union (s := A) (t := B)
  -- Transport the membership through this equality.
  have hx' : x ‚àà closure (interior A ‚à™ interior B) := by
    simpa [hInt] using hx
  -- Use the general fact that the closure of a union
  -- is contained in the union of the closures.
  have h_subset :
      closure (interior A ‚à™ interior B) ‚äÜ
        closure (interior A) ‚à™ closure (interior B) :=
    closure_union_subset (interior A) (interior B)
  exact h_subset hx'

theorem P2_iff_interiorClosureInterior_mem_nhds {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A ‚Üî ‚àÄ x ‚àà A, interior (closure (interior A)) ‚àà ùìù x := by
  classical
  constructor
  ¬∑ intro hP2 x hx
    have hx_mem : x ‚àà interior (closure (interior A)) := hP2 hx
    exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).1 hx_mem
  ¬∑ intro h
    dsimp [Topology.P2]
    intro x hx
    have hN : interior (closure (interior A)) ‚àà ùìù x := h x hx
    exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).2 hN
